The repository structure, plugin manifest format (`.claude-plugin/`),
skill organization pattern (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`), cold-start
interview pattern, and "draft for attorney review" disclaimer
discipline are adapted from Anthropic's claude-for-legal.

This derivative work adapts the architectural patterns and conventions
to Turkish legal practice (KVKK, SMK, TTK, TBB Meslek Kuralları, etc.).
Plugin content, terminology, legal framing, and example outputs are
original to this repository or contributed by the community.

Modifications include but are not limited to:
- Replacement of US/UK legal framework references (FMLA, USPTO, GDPR,
  ABA) with Turkish equivalents (4857 İş Kanunu, TÜRKPATENT, KVKK, TBB)
- Removal of all third-party MCP server dependencies
- Translation of all user-facing strings into Turkish
- New plugin: `kvkk-uyum-tr` (originally implemented for this project)
- New shared references: TBB Meslek Kuralları özet, baro danışma notu,
  karar atıf kuralları (halüsinasyon disiplini)

